%%%
Nested broadcast — outer kernel body is itself a broadcast.

Per-patient observations across visits: each patient has noise scale
sigma_p (varying across patients); each visit has baseline mean
visit_mean_v (varying across visits, shared across patients). The
outer kernel-broadcast iterates patients; per patient the kernel body
is itself a broadcast over visit_means with the patient's sigma.

Phase 4.4 lands the nested-broadcast composite-body recogniser + the
`_executeNestedBroadcastComposite` execution path with two-axis
per-cell iteration (outer K_outer * inner K_inner worker calls).

The lift's `inlineOnce` collapses simple `kernelof(<DistCall>, …)`
inner kernels into the inner broadcast as the bare DistCall ref, so
the canonical user surface (`broadcast(<simple_kernel>, args…)`
inside a kernelof body) reaches the recogniser as
`lawof(broadcast(<bare_dist>, kw))` — captured by the MVP scope.

Result shape per atom: [P, V] where P = patients, V = visits per
patient. Calibration: per-(p, v) cell mean ≈ visit_means[v]; per-(p,
v) cell variance ≈ sigmas_per_patient[p]^2.
%%%
flatppl_compat = "0.1"

% Per-visit baseline means (fixed, shared across patients).
visit_means = [10.0, 20.0, 30.0, 40.0]

% Per-patient noise scales.
sigmas_per_patient = [0.5, 1.0, 1.5]

% Inner observation kernel — `inlineOnce` collapses this into the
% inner broadcast's bare-dist head at lift time.
obs_kernel = kernelof(Normal(mu = mu, sigma = sigma),
                      mu = mu, sigma = sigma)

% Per-patient outer kernel: broadcast obs_kernel over visit_means
% with sigma_g (the patient's sigma) modulating the noise scale.
patient_kernel = kernelof(
  broadcast(obs_kernel, mu = visit_means, sigma = sigma_g),
  sigma_g = sigma_g)

% Kernel-broadcast over per-patient sigmas.
y = broadcast(patient_kernel, sigma_g = sigmas_per_patient)
